    <h1>The Spica Library</h1>
    <hr/>

    <p>Spica is a library of algorithms and data structures written in several languages. The
    contents of this library are intended to supplement the standard facilities of each
    language. This library also provides an opportunity to experiment with "advanced" or unusual
    algorithms and data structures that are not often seen in practice but that are still
    interesting.</p>

    <p>The algorithms and data structures that Spica covers are of the sort found in standard
    texts on the subject. This includes things like lists, trees, hash tables, graphs, sets,
    strings, sorting and searching methods, and so forth. In addition some components that
    support algorithm and data structure development are also included in Spica. For example,
    certain file manipulation, timing utilities, and debugging services are useful in writing
    algorithm test programs.</p>

